        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 6:57PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 655 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Six Flags Over Texas, or over western Grand Prairie and
eastern Arlington, moving southwest at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Worth, Arlington, Irving, Grand Prairie, Mansfield, Euless,
Burleson, Crowley, Forest Hill, Kennedale, Everman, Rendon, Edgecliff
Village, Pantego, Edgecliff, DFW Intl Airport, Dalworthington
Gardens, Lake Arlington, Mountain Creek Lake, and Joe Pool Lake.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 35W between mile markers 38 and 48.
Interstate 20 between mile markers 433 and 458.
Interstate 30 between mile markers 21 and 36.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
